MT Chairman of [[Tsingtao]]<ref name=\"Titles1\" />|years=1927&ndash;1929}}\n{{s-aft|after=[[Chen Tiao-yuan]]}}\n{{s-bef|before=?}}\n{{s-ttl|title=Acting [[Minister of Information]] of the Republic of China<ref name=\"Titles1\" />|years=1930&ndash;1937}}\n{{s-aft|after=?}}\n{{s-bef|before=?}}\n{{s-ttl|title=Commissioner of Education for [[Anhwei Province, Republic of China|Anhwei Province]] and [[Hupeh Province, Republic of China|Hupeh Province]]<ref name=\"Titles1\" />|years=1938&ndash;1939}}\n{{s-aft|after=?}}\n{{s-bef|before=Position created}}\n{{s-ttl|title=Chairman of the Transitional National Government Committee of the Ministry of Education<ref name=\"Titles1\" />|years=1940&ndash;1940}}\n{{s-aft|after=Position ended}}\n{{s-bef|before=?}}\n{{s-ttl|title=KMT Chairman of [[Chongqing|Chungking]]<ref name=\"Titles1\" />|years=1941&ndash;1945}}\n{{s-aft|after=?}}\n{{s-bef|before=[[Wu Shao-hsu]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=KMT Chairman of [[Shanghai]]<ref name=\"Titles1\" />|years=1946&ndash;25 May 1949}}\n{{s-aft|after=Shanghai Under Communist Control<br/>[[Chen Yi (general)|Chen Yi]]}}\n{{s-bef|before=[[Zhu Shaoliang]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=[[Secretary General]] & [[Acting Governor]] of [[Fujian Province, Republic of China|Fukien Province]]<br/>and<br/>KMT Chairman of Fukien Province<ref name=\"Titles1\" />|years=May 1949&ndash;November 1949}}\n{{s-aft|after=[[Hu Lien]]}}\n{{s-bef|before=Organization created}}\n{{s-ttl|title=[[Secretary General]] of the [[Free China Relief Association]]<ref name=\"Titles1\" /><ref name=\"Mandate to the National Assembly\"/><ref name=\"Ryukyu Islands United States Civil Administration, 1950-1972. Office of Public Information, Ryukyu Islands United States Civil Administration, 1950-1972. Office of Public Affairs, Ryukyu Islands United States Civil Administration, 1950-1972. Office of the High Commissioner, Ryukyu Islands United States Civil Administration, 1950-1972. Public Affairs Dept 1972\"/>|years=1949&ndash;1972}}\n{{s-aft|after=[[Ku Cheng-kang]]}}\n{{s-bef|before=[[Ku Cheng-kang]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=V President & Managing Director of the Free China Relief Association<ref name=\"Titles1\" />|years=1972&ndash;1988}}\n{{s-aft|after=?}}\n{{s-bef|before=Organization Created}}\n{{s-ttl|title=President of the [[Sino-Ryukyuan Cultural and Economic Association]]<ref name=\"Titles1\" /><ref name=\"Asian Outlook\"/>|years=1958&ndash;1988}}\n{{s-aft|after=David [[Chang Hsi-cheh]]<ref name=\"Foreign Broadcast Information Service 1988\"/>}}\n{{s-bef|before=Organization created}}\n{{s-ttl|title=Founder and Trustee of the [[Sino-Laotian Friendship Society]]|years=27 August 1959&ndash;?}}\n{{s-aft|after=?}}\n{{s-bef|before=Position created}}\n{{s-ttl|title=Secretary General of the Chinese National Committee for World Refugee Year<ref>{{cite news |last1= |first1= |last2= |first2= |date=1 May 1960 |title=A summary of important events from March 16 to April 15, 1960 |trans-title= |url=http://taiwantoday.tw/ct.asp?xItem=171483&ctNode=124 |language=English |newspaper=Taiwan Today |location=Taipei |access-date=11 April 2016 |quote= }}</ref>|years=1960&ndash;1960}}\n{{s-aft|after=Position ended}}\n{{s-bef|before=Various}}\n{{s-ttl|title=National Policy Advisor to President<ref name=\"Titles1\" />|years=?&ndash;1988}}\n{{s-aft|after=Various}}\n{{s-bef|before=Position created}}\n{{s-ttl|title=Vice President of the Free China Relief Association<ref name=\"T\u02bbai-wan Chih Nan\">{{cite book |last= |edition=Digitized 31 Jan 2008 |date=1988 |title=T\u02bbai-wan Chih Nan |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=SdVkAAAAIAAJ&dq=Ku+Cheng-kang+fang+chih&focus=searchwithinvolume&q=%22conducting+relief%22 |location=Taipei |publisher=China News |page=170 |via=University of California}}</ref>|years=1988&ndash;1989}}\n{{s-aft|after=?}}\n{{s-end}}\n\n== Notes ==\n\n{{Reflist|group=note}}\n\n== References ==\n\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Fang, Chih}}\n[[Category:1894 births]]\n[[Category:1989 deaths]]\n[[Category:Members of the Kuomintang]]\n[[Category:University of Tokyo alumni]]\n[[Category:University of Tsukuba alumni]]\n[[Category:Chinese anti-communists]]\n[[Category:Chinese military personnel of World War II]]\n[[Category:People of the Chinese Civil War]]\n[[Category:Kuomintang politicians in Taiwan]]\n[[Category:Republic of China (1912\u20131949)]]\n[[Category:Political office-holders in Shanghai]]\n[[Category:Political office-holders in Hubei]]\n[[Category:Political office-holders in Anhui]]\n[[Category:Political office-holders in Taiwan]]\n[[Category:Governors of Fujian]]\n[[Category:Political office-holders in Chongqing]]\n[[Category:Government ministers of China]]\n[[Category:Chinese Civil War refugees]]\n[[Category:Taiwanese people from Anhui]]\n[[Category:People from Tongcheng, Anhui]]\n", "text_old": "{{overly detailed|date=October 2018}}\n{{Infobox officeholder\n | honorific-prefix   =\n | name               = Fang Chih\n | native_name        = {{nobold|\u65b9\u6cbb}}\n | native_name_lang   = Chinese\n | honorific-suffix   = \n | image              = FangChiOkinawaMemorial1.jpg FangChiOkinawaMemorial5.JPG\n | image_size         = 220px\n | alt                = \n | caption            = The memorial to Fang Chih at [[Okinawa]].\n | order              = \n | office             =  KMT Chairman of [[Fujian Province, Republic of China|Fukien Province]]<ref name=\"Titles1\" />\n | term_start         = 1927\n | term_end           = 1929\n | president          = [[Chiang Kai-shek]]\n | governor           = [[Sa Chen-Ping]]<br/>[[Yang Shu-chuang]]\n | order2             =  \n | office2            =  KMT Chairman of [[Anhui Province|Anhwei Province]]<ref name=\"Titles1\" />\n | term_start2        =  1927\n | term_end2          =  1929\n | president2         =  [[Chiang Kai-shek]]\n | governor2          = [[Ch'en Tiao-yuan]]<br/>[[Han Kuo-chun]]\n | predecessor2       =  \n | successor2         =  \n | order3             =  \n | office3            =  KMT Chairman of [[Tsi