{"title_page": "Institute of Brunei Technical Education", "text_new": "{{Infobox university\n| name = Institute of Brunei Technical Education\n| native_name = '''Institut Pendidikan Teknikal Brunei'''\n| native_name_lang = ms\n| image = Institute of Brunei Technical Education logo.png\n| mottoeng = Inspiring Bruneians Towards Excellence\n| established =2014<ref name=\"moe\">{{cite web|url=http://moe.gov.bn/SitePages/Post%20Secondary%20Education.aspx|title=Ministry of Education, Brunei Darussalam - Post Secondary Education|publisher=moe.gov.bn|accessdate=2016-06-26}}</ref> \n| type = [[Vocational school|Vocational]]\n| chairman = Amin Liew Abdullah<ref name=\"ibte\">{{cite web|url=https://ibte.edu.bn/organisation-chart/|title=IBTE : Institute of Brunei Technical Education - Inspiring Bruneians Towards Excellence|author=IBTE|publisher=ibte.edu.bn|accessdate=2016-06-26}}</ref>\n| head_label = [[Chief executive officer|CEO]]\n| head = Chin, Wei Keh<ref name=\"ibte\">{{cite web|url=https://ibte.edu.bn/organisation-chart/|title=IBTE : Institute of Brunei Technical Education - Inspiring Bruneians Towards Excellence|author=IBTE|publisher=ibte.edu.bn|accessdate=2016-06-26}}</ref>\n| city = \n| province = [[Brunei-Muara District|Brunei-Muara]] & [[Belait District|Belait]]\n| country = [[Brunei]]\n| campus = Sultan Saiful Rijal, Nakhoda Ragam, Mechanical, Business, Jefri Bolkiah, Sultan Bolkiah & Agro-Technology\n| website = {{URL|https://ibte.edu.bn}}\n| coor = \n}}\nThe '''Institute of Brunei Technical Education''' ({{Lang-ms|'''Institut Pendidikan Teknikal Brunei'''}}; [[abbreviation]]: '''{{Abbr|IBTE|Institute of Brunei Technical Education}}''') is a post-secondary institution providing technical and vocational education in Brunei. IBTE was created on May 27, 2014<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://moe.gov.bn/SitePages/Post%2520Secondary%2520Education.aspx|title=Post Secondary Education|website=Ministry of Education, Brunei Darussalam|accessdate=2016-06-26}}</ref> from the merger of the Department of Technical Education and seven technical and vocational schools nationwide.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://ibte.edu.bn/prospectus/|title=eProspectus|website=Institute of Brunei Technical Education|accessdate=2016-06-26}}</ref>\n\n== Institutions ==\nSince 2016, the seven schools under IBTE have been restructured into two cluster of schools, namely '''IBTE Central''' and '''IBTE Satellite'''.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.bt.com.bn/news-national/2016/05/27/ibte-restructures-school-networks#sthash.E0lZuY9a.dpbs|title=IBTE restructures school networks|website=The Brunei Times|accessdate=2016-06-26}}{{Dead link|date=January 2020 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> The schools have also been renamed so as to reflect better their merger under one umbrella institution, taking up the terms 'IBTE' and 'Campus' as part of the new names.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://ibte.edu.bn/network-of-schools/|title=IBTE Network of Schools|website=Institute of Brunei Technical Education|accessdate=2016-06-26}}</ref>\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n!Cluster Name\n!Name\n!Former Name\n!Location (District)\n|-\n| rowspan=\"4\" |IBTE Central\n|[[IBTE Sultan Saiful Rijal Campus]]\n|Sultan Saiful Rijal Technical College\n| rowspan=\"4\" |[[Brunei-Muara District|Brunei-Muara]]\n|-\n|[[IBTE Nakhoda Ragam Campus]]\n|Nakhoda Ragam Vocational School\n|-\n|[[IBTE Mechanical Campus]]\n|Mechanic Training Centre\n|-\n|[[IBTE Business Campus]]\n|Business School\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\" |IBTE Satellite\n|[[IBTE Jefri Bolkiah Campus]]\n|Jefri Bolkiah College of Engineering\n| rowspan=\"2\" |[[Belait District|Belait]]\n|-\n|[[IBTE Sultan Bolkiah Campus]]\n|Sultan Bolkiah Vocational School\n|-\n|[[IBTE Agro-Technology Campus]]\n|Wasan Vocational School\n|[[Brunei-Muara District|Brunei-Muara]]\n|}\n\n== References ==\n<references />\n\n== External links ==\n* [https://ibte.edu.bn IBTE official website]\n{{Institute of Brunei Technical Education}}\n\n{{coord missing|Brunei}}\n\n{{Institution of Higher Learning in Brunei}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Universities and colleges in Brunei]]\n[[Category:Vocational education in Asia]]\n[[Category:2003 establishments in Brunei]]\n[[Category:Educational institutions established in 2014]]\n[[Category:2014 establishments in Brunei]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox university\n| name = Institute of Brunei Technical Education\n| native_name = '''Institut Pendidikan Teknikal Brunei'''\n| native_name_lang = ms\n| image = Institute of Brunei Technical Education logo.png\n| mottoeng = Inspiring Bruneians Towards Excellence\n| established =2014<ref name=\"moe\">{{cite web|url=http://moe.gov.bn/SitePages/Post%20Secondary%20Education.aspx|title=Ministry of Education, Brunei Darussalam - Post Secondary Education|publisher=moe.gov.bn|accessdate=2016-06-26}}</ref> \n| type = [[Vocational school|Vocational]]\n| chairman = Amin Liew Abdullah<ref name=\"ibte\">{{cite web|url=https://ibte.edu.bn/organisation-chart/|title=IBTE : Institute of Brunei Technical Education - Inspiring Bruneians Towards Excellence|author=IBTE|publisher=ibte.edu.bn|accessdate=2016-06-26}}</ref>\n| head_label = [[Chief executive officer|CEO]]\n| head = Chin, Wei Keh<ref name=\"ibte\">{{cite web|url=https://ibte.edu.bn/organisation-chart/|title=IBTE : Institute of Brunei Technical Education - Inspiring Bruneians Towards Excellence|author=IBTE|publisher=ibte.edu.bn|accessdate=2016-06-26}}</ref>\n| city = \n| province = [[Brunei-Muara District|Brunei-Muara]] & [[Belait District|Belait]]\n| country = [[Brunei]]\n| campus = Sultan Saiful Rijal, Nakhoda Ragam, Mechanical, Business, Jefri Bolkiah, Sultan Bolkiah & Agro-Technology\n| website = {{URL|https://ibte.edu.bn}}\n| coor = \n}}\nThe '''Institute of Brunei Technical Education''' ({{Lang-ms|'''Institut Pendidikan Teknikal Brunei'''}}; [[abbreviation]]: '''{{Abbr|IBTE|Institute of Brunei Technical Education}}''') is a post-secondary institution providing technical and vocational education in Brunei. IBTE was created on May 27, 2014<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://moe.gov.bn/SitePages/Post%2520Secondary%2520Education.aspx|title=Post Secondary Education|website=Ministry of Education, Brunei Darussalam|accessdate=2016-06-26}}</ref> from the merger of the Department of Technical Education and seven technical and vocational schools nationwide.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://ibte.edu.bn/prospectus/|title=eProspectus|website=Institute of Brunei Technical Education|accessdate=2016-06-26}}</ref>\n\n== Institutions ==\nSince 2016, the seven schools under IBTE have been restructured into two cluster of schools, namely '''IBTE Central''' and '''IBTE Satellite'''.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.bt.com.bn/news-national/2016/05/27/ibte-restructures-school-networks#sthash.E0lZuY9a.dpbs|title=IBTE restructures school networks|website=The Brunei Times|accessdate=2016-06-26}}{{Dead link|date=January 2020 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> The schools have also been renamed so as to reflect better their merger under one umbrella institution, taking up the terms 'IBTE' and 'Campus' as part of the new names.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://ibte.edu.bn/network-of-schools/|title=IBTE Network of Schools|website=Institute of Brunei Technical Education|accessdate=2016-06-26}}</ref>\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n!Cluster Name\n!Name\n!Former Name\n!Location (District)\n|-\n| rowspan=\"4\" |IBTE Central\n|[[IBTE Sultan Saiful Rijal Campus]]\n|Sultan Saiful Rijal Technical College\n| rowspan=\"4\" |[[Brunei-Muara District|Brunei-Muara]]\n|-\n|[[IBTE Nakhoda Ragam Campus]]\n|Nakhoda Ragam Vocational School\n|-\n|[[IBTE Mechanical Campus]]\n|Mechanic Training Centre\n|-\n|[[IBTE Business Campus]]\n|Business School\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\" |IBTE Satellite\n|[[IBTE Jefri Bolkiah Campus]]\n|Jefri Bolkiah College of Engineering\n| rowspan=\"2\" |[[Belait District|Belait]]\n|-\n|[[IBTE Sultan Bolkiah Campus]]\n|Sultan Bolkiah Vocational School\n|-\n|[[IBTE Agro-Technology Campus]]\n|Wasan Vocational School\