{"title_page": "Institute of Aviation Engineering and Technology", "text_new": "{{unreferenced|date=September 2014}}\n\n{{Infobox university\n|Sname              = \n|native_name       = \u0645\u0639\u0647\u062f \u0647\u0646\u062f\u0633\u0629 \u0648\u062a\u0643\u0646\u0648\u0644\u0648\u062c\u064a\u0627 \u0627\u0644\u0637\u064a\u0631\u0627\u0646 \n|image_name        = Iaet.jpg\n|image_size        = \n|caption           = \n|latin_name        =\n|motto             =\n|mottoeng          =\n|established       = {{start date and age|1997}}\n|type              = \n|affiliation       =\n|endowment         =\n|chancellor        =\n|president         = \n|dean              = Prof. Abdelkader Abdel Karim Ibrahim\n|faculty           = 98\n|staff             =\n|students          = 2000\n|undergrad         =\n|postgrad          =\n|doctoral          =\n|other             =\n|city              = [[Giza]]\n|province          = [[Giza Governorate|Giza]]\n|country           = [[Egypt]]\n|coor              = \n|campus            = \n|former_names      = \n|free_label        =\n|free              =\n|nickname          =\n|affiliations      =\n|website           = [http://www.iaet-eg.org/wp http://www.iaet-eg.org/wp]\n|logo              = \n|footnotes         =\n|name=}}\n\n'''Institute of Aviation Engineering and Technology''' (Arabic:\u0645\u0639\u0647\u062f \u0647\u0646\u062f\u0633\u0629 \u0648\u062a\u0643\u0646\u0648\u0644\u0648\u062c\u064a\u0627 \u0627\u0644\u0637\u064a\u0631\u0627\u0646) is an engineering technology institute in [[Giza]], [[Egypt]]. It is a private institute that belongs to the ministry of higher education in Egypt and under the academic supervision of the Faculty of Engineering, [[Cairo University]] .\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.iaet.edu.eg/ official website]\n* https://web.facebook.com/aviation.iaet/  Facebook page\n\n{{coord|30.0700|N|31.1887|E|source:wikidata|display=title}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Buildings and structures in Giza]]\n[[Category:Universities in Egypt]]\n", "text_old": "{{unreferenced|date=September 2014}}\n\n{{Infobox University\n|Sname              = \n|native_name       = \u0645\u0639\u0647\u062f \u0647\u0646\u062f\u0633\u0629 \u0648\u062a\u0643\u0646\u0648\u0644\u0648\u062c\u064a\u0627 \u0627\u0644\u0637\u064a\u0631\u0627\u0646 \n|image_name        = Iaet.jpg\n|image_size        = \n|caption           = \n|latin_name        =\n|motto             =\n|mottoeng          =\n|established       = {{start date and age|1997}}\n|type              = \n|affiliation       =\n|endowment         =\n|chancellor        =\n|president         = \n|dean              = Prof. Abdelkader Abdel Karim Ibrahim\n|faculty           = 98\n|staff             =\n|students          = 2000\n|undergrad         =\n|postgrad          =\n|doctoral          =\n|other             =\n|city              = [[Giza]]\n|province          = [[Giza Governorate|Giza]]\n|country           = [[Egypt]]\n|coor              = \n|campus            = \n|former_names      = \n|free_label        =\n|free              =\n|nickname          =\n|affiliations      =\n|website           = [http://www.iaet-eg.org/wp http://www.iaet-eg.org/wp]\n|logo              = \n|footnotes         =\n|name=}}\n\n'''Institute of Aviation Engineering and Technology''' (Arabic:\u0645\u0639\u0647\u062f \u0647\u0646\u062f\u0633\u0629 \u0648\u062a\u0643\u0646\u0648\u0644\u0648\u062c\u064a\u0627 \u0627\u0644\u0637\u064a\u0631\u0627\u0646) is an engineering technology institute in [[Giza]], [[Egypt]]. It is a private institute that belongs to the ministry of higher education in Egypt and under the academic supervision of the Faculty of Engineering, [[Cairo University]] .\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.iaet.edu.eg/ official website]\nhttps://web.facebook.com/aviation.iaet/  Facebook page\n\n{{coord|30.0700|N|31.1887|E|source:wikidata|display=title}}\n\n[[Category:Buildings and structures in Giza]]\n[[Category:Universities in Egypt]]\n", "name_user": "Ser Amantio di Nicolao", "label": "safe", "comment": "add authority control", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Institute_of_Aviation_Engineering_and_Technology"}
{"title_page": "CYP11B3", "text_new": "{{Infobox nonhuman protein\n| Name = cytochrome P450, family 11, subfamily b, polypeptide 3\n| image = \n| width = \n| caption = \n| Organism = Rattus norvegicus\n| TaxID = 19353\n| Symbol = CYP11B3\n| AltSymbols = \n| EntrezGene = 353498\n| HomoloGene = 106948\n| PDB = \n| RefSeqmRNA = NM_181824\n| RefSeqProtein = \n| UniProt = \n| Chromosome = rat chromosome 7\n| EntrezChromosome = \n| GenLoc_start = 116156219\n| GenLoc_end = 116255167\n}}\nThe '''Cyp11b3''' is a [[rat]] [[gene]] encoding a [[CYP450]] [[enzyme]], which is mainly expressed in [[neonatal]] rat [[adrenal]]s, and also expressed in a small amount in other organs of adult rats, this enzyme mainly catalyzing [[11-Deoxycorticosterone]] (DOC) to [[18-Hydroxy-11-deoxycorticosterone]] (18-OH-DOC).<ref>{{cite journal |last1=Zhou |first1=MY |last2=Gomez-Sanchez |first2=EP |last3=Foecking |first3=MF |last4=Gomez-Sanchez |first4=CE |title=Cloning and expression of the rat adrenal cytochrome P-450 11B3 (CYP11B3) enzyme cDNA: preferential 18-hydroxylation over 11 beta-hydroxylation of DOC. |journal=Molecular and cellular endocrinology |date=30 October 1995 |volume=114 |issue=1-2 |pages=137-45 |doi=10.1016/0303-7207(95)03653-o |pmid=8674838}}</ref>\nCyp11b3 gene is also located at [[Chromosome]] 7q34, next to rat [[CYP11B1]] and [[CYP11B2]].\n== References ==\n<references/>\n{{Cytochrome P450}}\n[[Category:Cytochrome P450|11]]\n[[Category:Mammal genes|rat]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox nonhuman protein\n| Name = cytochrome P450, family 11, subfamily b, polypeptide 3\n| image = \n| width = \n| caption = \n| Organism = Rattus norvegicus\n| TaxID = 19353\n| Symbol = CYP11B3\n| AltSymbols = \n| EntrezGene = 353498\n| HomoloGene = 106948\n| PDB = \n| RefSeqmRNA = NM_181824\n| RefSeqProtein = \n| UniProt = \n| Chromosome = rat chromosome 7\n| EntrezChromosome = \n| GenLoc_start = 116156219\n| GenLoc_end = 116255167\n}}\nThe '''Cyp11b3''' is a [[rat]] [[gene]] encoding a [[CYP450]] [[enzyme]], which is mainly expressed in [[neonatal]] rat [[adrenal]]s, and also expressed in a small amount in other organs of adult rats, this enzyme mainly catalyzing [[11-Deoxycorticosterone]] (DOC) to [[18-Hydroxy-11-deoxycorticosterone]] (18-OH-DOC).<ref>{{cite journal |last1=Zhou |first1=MY |last2=Gomez-Sanchez |first2=EP |last3=Foecking |first3=MF |last4=Gomez-Sanchez |first4=CE |title=Cloning and expression of the rat adrenal cytochrome P-450 11B3 (CYP11B3) enzyme cDNA: preferential 18-hydroxylation over 11 beta-hydroxylation of DOC. |journal=Molecular and cellular endocrinology |date=30 October 1995 |volume=114 |issue=1-2 |pages=137-45 |doi=10.1016/0303-7207(95)03653-o |pmid=8674838}}</ref>\nCyp11b3 gene is also located at [[Chromosome]] 7q34, next to [[CYP11B1]] and [[CYP11B2]].\n== References ==\n<references/>\n{{Cytochrome P450}}\n[[Category:Cytochrome P450|11]]\n[[Category:Mammal genes|rat]]\n", "name_user": "Htmlzycq", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/CYP11B3"}
{"title_page": "Institute of Advance Communication, Education and Research", "text_new": "{{Infobox college\n |name              = Institute of Advance Communication, Education and Research\n |native_name       = IACER\n |image_name        = IACER, Old Baneshwar.jpg\n |image_size        = \n |caption           = Campus Building\n |latin_name        = \n |established       = 2001\n |closed            = \n |type              = [[College]] \n |affiliation       = [[Pokhara University]]\n |endowment         = \n |rector            = \n |officer_in_charge = \n |chairman          = \n |chancellor        = \n |president         = \n |vice-president    = \n |superintendent    = \n |provost           = \n |vice_chancellor   = \n |principal         = Arun Gupto\n |dean              = \n |director          = \n |head_label        = \n |head              = \n |faculty           = 31\n |teachers           = \n |students          = 200+ \n |undergrad         = \n |postgrad          = \n |doctoral          = \n |other             = \n |city              = Bhimsenagola Marga , OLd Baneshwar, [[Kathmandu]] \n |state             =\n |province          = \n |country           = [[Nepal]]\n |campus            =  Town\n |former_names      = \n |free_label        = \n |free              = \n |sports            = \n |colors            = \n |colours           = \n |nickname          = \n |athletics         = \n |website           = [https://iacer.edu.np/ IACER.edu.np]\n |logo              = \n |footnotes         = \n}}\n\n'''IACER''' - '''Institute of Advance Communication, Education and Research''' is a researched based college situated in [[Kathmandu]], [[Nepal]]. It is established in 2001 and it is affiliated to [[Pokhara University]].<ref name=\"A1\">{{cite news |url=https://thehimalayantimes.com/entertainment/an-institute-with-a-difference/ |title=An Institute with a difference |work=[[The Himalayan Times]] |location=Kathmandu |publisher=International Media Network Nepal (Pvt) Ltd |da